<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

<p>
    At JKLHealthcare, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our services.
</p>

<h3>1. Information Collection</h3>
<p>
    We collect information when you register as a patient, book appointments, or log in to your account. This information includes your name, email, contact number, address, and appointment details.
</p>

<h3>2. Use of Information</h3>
<p>
    We use your information to manage appointments, communicate with you about services, and improve our offerings. Your data may be used for:
    <ul>
        <li>Account creation and authentication</li>
        <li>Appointment scheduling and reminders</li>
        <li>Improving service quality</li>
    </ul>
</p>

<h3>3. Data Protection</h3>
<p>
    We use encryption and secure protocols to store and transmit your data. Passwords are hashed and never stored in plain text.
</p>

<h3>4. Sharing of Information</h3>
<p>
    We do not share your personal information with third parties except when necessary for legal compliance or as required by law.
</p>

<h3>5. Access to Your Information</h3>
<p>
    You have the right to access, modify, or delete your information. Contact us at customer.service@jklhealthcare.com if you need assistance.
</p>

<h3>6. Changes to Privacy Policy</h3>
<p>
    We may update this policy periodically. Please review it regularly to stay informed about how we protect your data.
</p>

<p>
    For any questions or concerns, please contact us at customer.service@jklhealthcare.com.
</p>
